DATA CLOUD
Use Data Cloud Data in Tableau

Tableau enables metadata and data discovery of all objects in your Data Cloud instance with Salesforce security mode.

The Data Cloud Tableau connector provides two modes for interacting between products: live and extract. You can select your mode in Tableau when setting up your connection by choosing the Live or Extract radio buttons available for selection after a table has been dragged into the “Need More data?” section.

Live mode is the default, but each mode has its own set of advantages and disadvantages.

All Data Cloud objects are accessible in Tableau by querying the authorized tenant and exposing the objects to Tableau after authentication is complete. 

To build Tableau visualizations from unified data, identity link files are required to be included in the mapping in Tableau.

Data Cloud Objects in Tableau

Mapping Unified Individual Data Model Objects

Use a Tableau relationship when you define a relationship between a Unified Individual Data Model Object (DMO) and DMOs that represent performance and interaction data from Marketing Cloud Engagement or cases from Service Cloud. You must also map the individual identity link using Tableau join for every engagement entity.

Downloading Tableau Data Source File

You can download already modeled relationships for your selected data object from Data Cloud. You can download the data models in the form of a Tableau data source file and import it for data exploration.

Fully Qualified Keys in Tableau

Fully Qualified Keys (FQKs) are composite keys that are used as the primary keys in Data Cloud. FQKs help resolve key conflicts that arise when data from different source systems is brought into Data Cloud.
